<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">
  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFrameworks>netstandard2.0;net45;net461</TargetFrameworks>
	<GenerateAssemblyInfo>true</GenerateAssemblyInfo>
	<GeneratePackageOnBuild>false</GeneratePackageOnBuild>
	<PackageId>Pipelines.Net</PackageId>
	<Authors>Sergey Solomentsev</Authors>
	<Company>Witty Lion</Company>
	<Description>Library that exposes SOLID principles by introducing pipelines.</Description>
	<Copyright>Witty Lion © 2018</Copyright>
	<PackageLicenseUrl>https://github.com/wittylion/Pipelines.Net/blob/master/LICENSE.txt</PackageLicenseUrl>
	<PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/wittylion/Pipelines.Net</PackageProjectUrl>
	<RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/wittylion/Pipelines.Net</RepositoryUrl>
	<RepositoryType>git</RepositoryType>
	<PackageReleaseNotes>
      New in this version:

      - Added new processors:

      * EnsurePropertyProcessor - processor that simply gets a key of the property and value to be added then adds key and value to the PipelineContext if the key doesn't exist;
      * ExecuteActionForPropertyProcessor - processor that executes action for property if it is found in the PipelineContext;
      * ExecuteActionForPropertyOrAbortProcessor - processor that executes action for property if it is found in the PipelineContext, or if property was not found aborts the pipeline;
      * ExecuteForEachElementInPropertyProcessor - processor that tries to get a collection of elements in property and then execute and action for each element;
	  * TryExecuteActionForPropertyProcessor - processor that tries to find a given property and if it is found executes a given action, if action fails exception handler (that can be passed to class) will be executed.
	  
	  - Added new helpful classes:
	  
	  * CommonProcessors - pack of static methods that simply provide you a needed processor;
	  * ProcessorConstructor - an adjustable constructor, which can be injected to other instances and provide a variety of processors;
	  * ConstructablePipeline - a pipeline with an instance of ProcessorConstructor, allows to faster create processors from provided templates.

      - Added new frameworks: .net core v2+, .net v4.5+
	</PackageReleaseNotes>
	<NeutralLanguage>English</NeutralLanguage>
	<PackageTags>Pipelines SOLID Processors Chain</PackageTags>
	<Version>1.1.2</Version>
	<AssemblyVersion>1.1.2.0</AssemblyVersion>
  </PropertyGroup>
</Project>